meta {
  name: Ingest
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

post {
  url: {{base_url}}/ingest
  body: multipartForm
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{bearer_token}}
}

body:multipart-form {
  patient_id: {{patient_pid}}
  doc_type: lab_pdf
  patient_uuid: {{patient_id}}
  file: @file(../eval/fixtures/maria_gonzalez_lab.pdf)
}

docs {
  The intake-extractor worker's standalone HTTP entry point (W2_ARCHITECTURE.md Section 2) -- upload
  -> dedup -> Claude vision extraction -> schema validation -> persist, all in one call, independent
  of any chat turn. `patient_id` here is the OpenEMR-native int pid (opposite of /chat's patient_id,
  which is the FHIR uuid) -- see agent/app/ingestion.py's docstrings for why the two write paths
  this calls into (medication vs. allergy endpoints) key the patient differently.

  `patient_uuid` is only required when doc_type=intake_form (the allergy endpoint needs it); safe to
  always include it as shown here.
}
